Czech Stocks Gain as New World Resources Jumps Most in 4 Months

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-05-04T15:38:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/czech-stocks-gain-as-new-world-resources-jumps-most-in-4-months.html
The Czech Republic’s benchmark equity
index rose today, erasing most of yesterday’s drop, as  New World
Resources NV (NWR)  had its biggest rally in almost four months and  CEZ
AS (CEZ)  and  Komercni Banka AS (KOMB)  advanced.  The PX gauge of 15 companies advanced 0.8 percent to
1,272.9 at its 4:28 p.m. close in  Prague , after losing 1 percent
yesterday.  NWR, the country’s largest coking-coal producer, jumped 3.6
percent to 290.1 koruna, its biggest one-day gain since Jan. 11.
CEZ, the biggest power utility, rose 0.9 percent to 944 koruna,
and Komercni, the Czech unit of Societe Generale SA, added 0.8
percent to 4,335 koruna, its highest close since April 11.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  